%N A101823 Indices of primes in sequence defined by A(0) = 31, A(n) = 10*A(n-1) - 9 for n > 0.
%C A101823 Numbers n such that 30*10^n + 1 is prime.
%C A101823 Numbers n such that digit 3 followed by n >= 0 occurrences of digit 0 followed by digit 1 is prime.
%D A101823 Klaus Brockhaus and Walter Oberschelp, Zahlenfolgen mit homogenem Ziffernkern, MNU 59/8 (2006), pp. 462-467.
%H A101823 Makoto Kamada, <a href="https://stdkmd.net/nrr/3/30001.htm#prime">Prime numbers of the form 300...001</a>.
%F A101823 a(n) = A056807(n) - 1.
%e A101823 3001 is prime, hence 2 is a term.
%o A101823 (PARI) a=31;for(n=0,2000,if(isprime(a),print1(n,","));a=10*a-9)
%o A101823 (PARI) for(n=0,2000,if(isprime(30*10^n+1),print1(n,",")))
